tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Best season outing was a T25 at The Players Cup in July.

2014: Finished fifth thanks to rounds of 64-64 on the weekend at the SIGA Dakota Dunes Open. Ninth career top-10 finish in sixth season on PGA TOUR Canada. 

2013: Shot a first-round 63 and led through 36 holes on the way to a T4 finish at the season-opening Times Colonist Island Savings Open.

2012: Posted five top-20 finishes for the year and finished seventh on the Order of Merit...Lost in a playoff to Michael Gligic at the ATB Financial Classic presented by TELUS...Played in the PGA TOUR's Frys.com Open. 

2011: Had a consistent year, making seven cuts including a T7 at the Syncrude Boreal Open. Played in the Frys.com Open on the PGA TOUR.

2010: Had a pair of top-10s, including T5 at the ATB Financial Classic...Was also T8 at the Desert Dunes Classic...Made his Web.com Tour debut, finishing T41 at the Cox Classic in Nebraska.

2009: Started his rookie season slowly but picked up the pace toward the end with three consecutive top-25 finishes, including a season-ending T4 at Nayarit. Earned exempt card at the Spring Qualifying School.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the 2008 Northern California Amateur and was the Northern California Golf Association Player of the Year. Advanced to the second stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying School and won the pre-qualifying stage by 12 shots at 16-under par...Also participated in match play at the U.S. Amateur.
tourBios.personal: Has a wine label with two older brothers called Marshall Davis... Lists playing in his first PGA TOUR event as his biggest thrill in golf...Hobbies include fly fishing and watching sports...Lists fly fishing in Alaska with his dad as his biggest thrill outside golf...Favorite course played is Spyglass Hill...Always marks ball with a U.S. quarter...Favorite pro teams are the San Francisco 49ers, San Jose Sharks and Seattle Mariners...Favorite foods are pasta, pizza and ice cream...Favorite cities to visit are San Jose, Portland, Chicago, Victoria and Montreal... Dream foursome would actually be a fivesome, with his dad, grandfather and two brothers.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was 2nd in 2012 at the ATB Financial Classic presented by TELUS.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 84th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
